cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.SY

This paper deals with the problem of computing integrals of linearly constrained multivariate Gaussian densities, which is a common problem in machine learning and statistics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also presents an algorithm that uses geometry to estimate integrals, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Additionally, the paper uses Bayesian optimization, which is a common topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves probability theory and conditional probabilities, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper deals with optimization and control, which could place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control).
